==Old English==

===Noun===
'''dǣġe'''
# a female servant
# a woman in charge of a [[dairy]]

====Etymology====
From Germanic ''*deigjōn'' ‘kneader’: cognate with Old Norse [[deigja]] ‘female servant’.

====Pronunciation====
[[IPA]]: /'dæ:je/

[[Category: Old English nouns]]


===Inflexion===
'''dæġe''': dative singular of [[dæg|dæġ]].

====Pronunciation====
[[IPA]]: /'dæje/